# Starter Configuration Templates (Ready to Use)

These files are pre-configured to handle your exact stack and can be copied directly into your folders.

### Template 1: `.env.example`
Put this file in your root folder. It tells other developers what keys they need to set up in their local configurations.

```text
# ==========================================
# LLM SHIELD PLATFORM - ENVIRONMENT TEMPLATE
# ==========================================

# Core Application Settings
ENVIRONMENT=dev
PROJECT_NAME="LLM Shield Platform"

# Supabase Configurations
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres:[YOUR_PASSWORD]@aws-0-us-east-1.pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres"
SUPABASE_URL="https://your-supabase-project.supabase.co"
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY="your-anon-public-key"

# Security & Secrets
JWT_SECRET_KEY="generate-a-secure-64-character-string-for-prod"

# Third-Party Integrations
RESEND_API_KEY="re_123456789_MockApiKeyForDevelopment"